        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 26 at 3:53PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 352 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rooster Rock, or 12 miles south of Mexican Hat, moving northeast at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mexican Hat and Halchita.

This includes U.S. Highway 163 in Utah between mile markers 10 and
28.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
